First Lady Jill Biden delivered a speech in Chicago, Illinois, expressing her support for unions and highlighting the importance of workers and their contributions to the country. She emphasized that unions are at the center of President Joe Biden's vision to rebuild the economy "from the bottom up and the middle out." Biden shared personal stories about her husband's upbringing in a working-class family and her own father's experience as an immigrant. She praised the role of unions in building the middle class and fighting for better pay, safer working conditions, flexibility, and healthcare. Biden also mentioned the achievements of the Biden administration, such as job creation, infrastructure investment, and growth in clean energy and manufacturing. She thanked the elected leaders and labor advocates present and expressed her and the president's unwavering support for unions.